{
  "texts": [
    "Through the squeeze operation, it aggregates global information across the entire spatial domain of the feature map.",
    "Then, during the excitation phase, it selectively emphasizes important feature channels while suppressing irrelevant ones.",
    "This recalibration ensures that the network allocates more attention to the most informative channels, thereby improving the overall feature extraction process.",
    "This mechanism helps address the limitation of CNNs that often fail to prioritize key features crucial for remote sensing image classification.The integration of the SE network within the residual structure of the RCA network is thus a strategic choice that combines the spatial feature extraction capabilities of CNNs with the adaptive focus provided by channel attention.",
    "The collaboration between the residual connections and the SE mechanism results in enhanced spatial and channel-wise feature extraction."
  ]
}